From f1de20b09a773806ade7ef359a7546cebd6f05df Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Murat Sezgin <msezgin@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Oct 2025 20:58:03 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] qca-nss-ecm: don't stop traversing node chain in FDB handler

Each node instance is bound to an interface. If there are both bridge and
routed flows from a client connected to a bridge port, two node instances
may exist for the client's MAC address. One is bound to the bridge port for
bridge connections, and the other is bound to the bridge interface for routed
connections.

Keep traversing the chain so both node instances are handled.

Change-Id: I0330ac6d07dbc17ca67510dc0e677f54347adb49
Signed-off-by: Murat Sezgin <msezgin@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 ecm_interface.c | 5 -----
 1 file changed, 5 deletions(-)

--- a/ecm_interface.c
+++ b/ecm_interface.c
@@ -8092,11 +8092,6 @@ void ecm_interface_node_connections_defu
 					ecm_db_traverse_node_connection_list_and_defunct(ni, dir, ip_version, type);
 				}
 			}
-			/*
-			 * node was found and connections are destroyed, we are done.
-			 */
-			ecm_db_node_deref(ni);
-			break;
 		}
 
 		/*
